From 11cea5f96b3f404a60a6a5f97d53307de0c91153 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sandbox <sandbox@local>
Date: Fri, 17 Jul 2026 15:12:42 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat: add Settings page as the central control panel

New route at /dashboard-v2/settings, built with the existing
DashboardLayout, Header and the same monochrome design language used
across every other Dashboard V2 module - no layout, header, colors,
radius, shadows or motion conventions changed.

16 sections per spec: hero with monochrome settings illustration and
floating status pills, account settings, preferences, notification
toggles (8 categories), privacy settings, security overview,
connected accounts, AI preferences toggles, dashboard preferences
toggles, data & storage breakdown, activity log, appearance (UI only),
help & support, about, a clearly separated danger zone with restrained
red accents, and quick navigation linking to all 8 other modules.

Added a small shared ToggleSwitch primitive (spring-animated, used by
Notifications / Privacy / AI Preferences / Dashboard Preferences)
instead of duplicating toggle markup four times.

Sidebar updated directly (Settings item now links to its route).

UI only - no backend, API, auth, or real settings persistence -
realistic dummy data throughout.
